conbody.p:
The attributes that are used for context hooks are:
@appid An ID used by an application to identify the topic.
@ua-context-string Contains the value of a user assistance (Help) context-string used to identify the topic.
@ua-source-priority Contains a value which indicates the precedence of context hooks in the map and context hooks in the topic. (This usage is defined when the attribute is used on resourceid within a DITA map; using this attribute on resourceid within a topic is undefined and reserved for future use.)
@ua-windowref Contains the name of the window to be used to display the Help topic, with that window's characteristics separately defined in a <ua-window> element in the DITA map.

The <ua-window> element provides attributes of @top,
          @left, @height, @width,
          @on-top, @features, @relative, and
          @full-screen.
